[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring javap's capabilities**\n\nI'm trying to think through whether the javap tool can decompile signatures. It's an interesting question because javap is typically used for disassembling Java class files, which might include some signature information. So, I wonder if it can effectively reverse these signatures into a human-readable format. I’ll need to dig a bit deeper to clarify its specific functionalities regarding signatures versus other components of Java classes. Let's get to the bottom of this!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0c3ac969b4df79e5016a42838b930c81938fe7fa3856b8d64b\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqQoONqLd-MX_rl68nByhYZBwQ1N6bPynjhtD1rlJnSu_U-asxI6ooKKN5ANrwEZm25wlvkA1yCXNy3SPrc7imqkPFB9Ymck4uCwZoX7OaAs7Z_fUPejTVerKHH6EUqUHUyLWmFZDLUOKAMcYHb4XevOoMIYV41YMl-DhI9aQBnikgYIpfVUXCMDdsgIRL37DwRIaJQhR7ZdeCQX0YuD-jb6hTgiMU05gQ2uE3DMNgiKaFbMIn11qPTMzLwNzdFHuPIWt4gNwMp5SbyfmiIqRPo72RPJ-W5PlJJMMCzvxePVGMraA7i1pIB5uHF7hgQM5axECys3r3JJs2EDo4RTBkF-Tm6dBiUOrnoPdnr9HwyZffiJzR-mqhfT5jOwN9GRz4gybFtqMiCV_bNb91O9QkcyXPBm4aQGu1BSyfxzSE9l8iho__sudHxqI38lbXozZYB3_6I1-8tOwi1_021MhXRGgsgGi_zzKP-qTOEJ55PIRUsD9pYZi891lEgRKUbeEyDK7K-28QDXn8TAwyjx3xjtzXBtscnocdNohG7AQ2blbaZrGyD7bu71VnVL_zxYsSg7XWZ3QRwm2hfOc4wMvqMmdUG5gNyyuA9gFk3vw1MBJrPKVwnXLbXOx30RcmYzeqt0-M41k6Gk-7j5_pESNWY-v7m23NBrgJUqS56XraZfoy96artmBN7hB6liKy5XsSjMD01GdiCUWHSejFl9rDHpxG_7g9a8K0HwdjD9ELvtT6pMJ8kgeHht-KFSdqh4Q19Ix-sbn6VTxWTutwEc97I14JxFuO0Ojiq3gMeIKm23O2Yc5qIWhpWtCu1NluChedhZfyzydDC3Ny8srMsM3rY5wCChll0TlBURDt_EjelEt9pGg4LhS7VXUb_lVajOsFjxWMoNgP0YP4d41OhHk3mEwl2P2CPRhKXWokQ5DF8xXCcbfo04VgUloT3ruQJHJylQv9ir5279hey7GKG9eqJxvHwg==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring javap's capabilities**\\n\\nI'm trying to think through whether the javap tool can decompile signatures. It's an interesting question because javap is typically use